org.eel.kitchen.jsonschema.report

Class ValidationMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eel.kitchen.jsonschema.report.ValidationMessage

  • public final class ValidationMessage
extends Object
    One validation message

    A validation message consists of three mandatory fields and optional information. The three mandatory fields are:

    • the validation domain (see ValidationDomain);
    • the associated keyword;
    • the validation message.

    You cannot instantiate this class directly: you need to use ValidationMessage.Builder for that.

    This class is immutable.

    See Also:
    ValidationMessage.Builder, ValidationReport
